OL,5, The UK government could be delivering  
OL,6, disability living allowance and some   
OL,7, other devolved benefits in Scotland for
OL,8, another three years until 2026.        
OL,10,FWork and Pensions Secretary Mel Stride 
OL,11,Fhas written to the Scottish government 
OL,12,Fto extend transitional arrangements.   
OL,14,FNew devolved powers in 2016 gave the   
OL,15,FScottish Parliament responsibility for 
OL,16,F#2.8bn of social security expenditure. 
OL,18,FThe Scottish government said it was    
OL,19,F"always a joint programme of delivery" 
OL,20,Fbetween both governments.              
